    "The easily-dehulled type Tartary buckwheat is a unique landrace used for steaming as a staple food, wine-and tea-making in areas settled by the Wa people.",
    "Its easily dehulled nature of EDT allows local Wa people to use ancient artificial wooden mortars and pestles to dehull Tartary buckwheat and steam together with rice as staple food to prevent lysine deficiency."
